<HEADLINE> Astros Drop Johnson, Call Up Miller </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Houston Astros optioned infielder Russ  
Johnson to Triple-A New Orleans on Monday and called up 
right-hander Wade Miller. 
</P>
<P>
	Miller was 9-5 with a 4.01 as a starter for New Orleans. He  
could start on Wednesday if Mike Hampton isn't able to go. Miller, 
22, has never pitched in the major leagues. 
</P>
<P>
	Hampton was scratched from his scheduled start on Monday against  
the Cincinnati Reds because of a sore pitching wrist, which he 
strained during batting practice last week. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson appeared in 54 games and batted .222 with one homer and  
six RBIs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
