<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pirates Recall Haad; Kendall Hurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- The Pittsburgh Pirates on Monday recalled  
Yamid Haad, a catcher who was playing in Single-A a week ago, as a 
replacement for injured Jason Kendall. 
</P>
<P>
	Kendall shattered and dislocated his right ankle when he tripped  
over first base Sunday. He is expected to miss the rest of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Kendall, who was fifth in the NL batting race with a .332  
average, was placed on the disabled list Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Haad will back up Keith Osik, who now becomes the starting  
catcher. Haad was 3-for-17 at Double-A Altoona after joining the 
team from Class A Lynchburg June 28. Haad hit .254 with five homers 
and 33 RBIs at Lynchburg. 
</P>
<P>
	Osik never has started regularly in the majors. He had only 40  
at-bats this season going into Monday's game against the Chicago 
Cubs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
