<HEADLINE> Hampton Skips Start With Sore Wrist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Houston Astros starter Mike Hampton was  
scratched from his scheduled start Monday because of a sore 
pitching wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Hampton, 10-3, hurt the wrist during batting practice a few days  
ago and it was still sore Monday. Interim manager Matt Galante said 
Hampton would be given a few more days' rest. 
</P>
<P>
	About two hours before the first pitch, the Astros announced  
that Chris Hold (1-8) would start in Hampton's place. 
</P>
<P>
	The Astros already are short one starter. Sean Bergman was  
placed on the disabled list Saturday and Scott Elarton was moved 
out of the bullpen to take his place in the rotation. Elarton is 
expected to remain a starter at least through the All-Star break. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
