<DOCNO> APW19990705.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-05 15:10:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Behrens Wins Graded Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Behrens took another forward step in his Horse  
of the Year bid with an impressive 2 3/4-length victory in the 
$400,000 Grade I Suburban Handicap on a hot and humid Monday at 
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the fourth straight for the 5-year-old horse. The  
others were in the Grade II Mass' Cap at Suffolk Downs May 29, 
Grade I Oaklawn Handicap April 3 at Oaklawn Park and the Grade I 
Gulfstream Park Handicap Feb. 27. 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens covered 1 1/4 miles in 2:01 on the fast track to earn  
$240,000 for Budlein Stable and William L. Clifton. He paid $2.60, 
$2.30 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Catienus paid $9.10 and $2.10, and Social Charter was $2.10.  
</P>
<P>
	Ridden aggressively by Jorge Chavez while carrying high weight  
of 121 pounds, Behrens was kept close to the pace early, took over 
with three furlongs remaining, and went the rest of the way 
unthreatened. 
</P>
<P>
	The order of finish was completed by Golden Missile, Well Noted,  
Baytown, Hanarsaan and Brushing Up. 
</P>
<P>
	Winning trainer H. James Bond acknowledged that he had been  
concerned about the oppressive heat and its possible effect on 
Behrens but said ``This is one heck of a horse.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm probably the luckiest man in the world to have this horse  
in training,'' Bond added. ``He's getting better and better. This 
is his distance.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens next start, however, will be the 1 1/8-mile Whitney Aug. 1  
at Saratoga in which he is scheduled to meet the tough Victory 
Gallop. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's coming to our home court,'' Bond said. ``Behrens likes  
Saratoga, and he'll be pretty tough up there.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
