<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Heritage of Gold Wins Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Heritage of Gold came from last place to  
post a 4 1/4-length victory over Harpia in the $300,000 Molly Pitcher 
Breeders' Cup Handicap at Monmouth Park on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Heritage of Gold, who was ridden by Casey Lambert, has won five  
straight starts and covered the 1 1/16 miles for 3-year-olds and up 
in 1:41.3. Heritage of Gold paid $11, $5 and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Harpia, ridden by Richard Migliore, paid $5.60 and $3.20, while  
favored Tap to Music, ridden by Pat Day, was $2.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Heritage of Gold has won five of her six starts this year. She  
has career earnings of $451,980 in 14 lifetime tries. 
</P>
<P>
	In Monday's $45,000 Decathlon Stakes, Lou's Bucks held off  
Special Occasion to win by a neck. 
</P>
<P>
	Trained by John Conner and ridden by Calixto Juarez, Lou's Bucks  
returned $9.40 covering the five furlongs in 56.2 seconds. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
