<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Magicalmysterycat Gives Lukas Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Magicalmysterycat defeated She's Classy  
by three lengths to win Monday's $103,096 Landaluce Stakes, giving 
trainer D. Wayne Lukas his sixth victory in the Grade II race at 
Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Magicalmysterycat, ridden by Chris Antley, covered six furlongs  
in 1:11 and paid $4 and $2.60. She's Classy returned $2.80 to 
place. There was no show wagering because of the four-horse field. 
Princes Melissa was another length back in third and Desert End was 
fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	``Her natural speed was good enough to get the lead,'' Antley  
said. ``Right now, of all the 2-year-old fillies who have shown 
themselves, she's right near the top. So far, her ability has been 
enough to keep her unbeaten.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $63,120, increased Magicalmysterycat's career  
earnings to $132,780. She's undefeated in three races. 
</P>
<P>
	Lukas won the Landaluce, renamed for the undefeated filly he  
trained, for the sixth time and first since he saddled Serena's 
Song in 1994. Landaluce died of a blood disorder in 1983 and is 
buried in the track's infield. She won the race, then called the 
Hollywood Lassie Stakes, by 21 lengths in 1983 and set the stakes 
record of 1:08. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was probably the most brilliant horse we've ever been  
around,'' Lukas said. ``Every once in a while when we're feeling a 
little down, we plug in that old tape and watch her waltz down 
through there like she did in this race.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
