<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> China 5, Norway 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- China coach Ma Yuanan doesn't expect the  
Wo,0573men's World Cup final to be a repeat of his team's Fourth 
of July humbling of Norway.  
</P>
<P>
	He'd be happy enough if it was a repeat of April 25.  
</P>
<P>
	That's the last time China met the United States team that it  
will face again in Saturday's World Cup gold medal game in 
Pasadena, Calif. And China won that one 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
	``China has beaten the U.S.A. already twice (this year),''  
Norway coach Per-Mathias Hogmo said Sunday after China shut out the 
Norwegians 5-0 at Foxboro Stadium to advance to the championship. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think they will be the favorites in the final. But they will  
meet a very enthusiastic U.S. team. So I think that will be an 
interesting fight.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Liu Ailing and Sun Wen scored two goals apiece -- scoring once  
each in the first 14 minutes to give China control early on a hot, 
sweaty night. The Chinese took a 3-0 lead six minutes into the 
second half on Liu's second goal, which was assisted by Sun. 
</P>
<P>
	And Norway still hadn't gotten a shot on goal.  
</P>
<P>
	``We were able to dictate the way the game was played,'' China  
goalkeeper Gao Hong said. ``We play with a sense of spiritual 
unity.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That was enough to win by the biggest margin in World Cup  
semifinal history and match the largest defeat in Norway soccer 
history. The loss left the Norwegians out of the final for the 
first time in the three World Cups. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had no possibility to show our best'' because of the early  
deficit, said Norway defender Linda Medalen, whose team will play 
for third place against Brazil, a 2-0 loser to the United States 
earlier Sunday in San Jose, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	The championship game will be a rematch of the 1996 Olympic gold  
medal game that the United States won 2-1. Since then, the teams 
have met six more times, with the United States holding the 
advantage, three games to two, with one tie. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's no doubt that the United States is one of the  
strongest teams in the world,'' the Chinese coach said. ``But the 
Chinese have played them three times (this year) and hold a 2-1 
advantage.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Americans will have a tough time if China dominates the ball  
as it did Sunday in stopping Norway's 10-game World Cup winning 
streak -- a streak that dates to the final of the 1991 tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	``It will be a hard game'' for the Americans, said the  
34-year-old defender, who is one of three Norway players remaining 
from the 1991 team. ``The two best teams are in the final, no doubt 
about that. ... I look forward to seeing (it).'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gao, the Chinese keeper, was rarely tested in the first half  
when Norway was outshot 11-0. The Norwegians had a 12-9 shooting 
advantage in the second half as they substituted and strategized to 
increase their offense, to no avail. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, China closed in often on Norwegian keeper Bente  
Nordby, scoring on its first two chances with goals by Sun in the 
third minute and Liu in the 14th. 
</P>
<P>
	Six minutes into the second half, Liu scored again with a  
12-yard left-footed volley after a Norwegian defender tried to 
clear a corner kick into the box. Fan Yunjie made it 4-0 in the 
65th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Sun also scored on a penalty kick after a hand ball in the box  
in the 72nd minute to tie Sissi of Brazil for the tournament lead 
with seven goals. 
</P>
<P>
	``She hasn't thought about that (the scoring lead) at all,'' Sun  
said through an interpreter. ``Her whole outlook has been to play 
with the team and to win.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
