<HEADLINE> Texas Doctor Kills Ex-Wife, Self </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SOUTHLAKE, Texas (AP) -- A man who recently lost custody of his  
daughters shot his ex-wife to death during her morning jog Monday 
and then killed himself. 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives believe Dr. Scott Chester Stone, of Tarboro, N.C.,  
hid in a wooded area to wait for his wife, Dr. Marisa Deneen 
Jackson. She and the couple's daughters, ages 6 and 8, had been 
staying in this upscale Fort Worth suburb with Stone's sister. 
</P>
<P>
	``Obviously, he probably knew (the morning jog) was a regular  
thing for her,'' police spokesman Robert Finn said. 
</P>
<P>
	A divorce court in North Carolina awarded custody of the girls  
to their mother last week. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the conditions of the custody agreement was that he  
could have the girls for six weeks in the summer,'' Finn said. 
</P>
<P>
	However, police said Stone did not tell his wife or his sister  
he was coming to Southlake. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
