<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kiraly: All-Time Volleyball Winner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Karch Kiraly came to Chicago tied for the most  
wins in professional beach volleyball history. He left alone at the 
top. 
</P>
<P>
	With the win Sunday in the Association of Volleyball  
Professionals-Paul Mitchell US Open, the 38-year-old Kiraly has 140 
career victories -- one more than Sinjin Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	The top-seeded team of Kiraly and Adam Johnson advanced through  
the loser's bracket to the finals where they defeated the 
fifth-seeded Brazilian team of Roberto Lopes and Franco Neto, 15-7. 
</P>
<P>
	On the women's side, the top-seeded team of Liz Masakayan and  
Elaine Youngs defeated the third-seeded team of Annett 
Buckner-Davis and Jenny Johnson-Jordan 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
	Each winning team took home dlrs 18,000 in prize money.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
