<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Stocks Lower at Midday / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar slipped against the yen Tuesday as  
traders stayed cautious after central bank intervention the 
previous day. Japanese stocks fell marginally. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 122.17 yen at midday, down 0.41 yen from late  
Monday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 11.21 points,  
or 0.06 percent, to close the morning session at 18,123.85. On 
Monday, the average closed up 202.59 points, or 1.13 percent, 
finishing at 18,135.06 -- its highest closing level since September 
1997. 
</P>
<P>
	In foreign exchange, the dollar traded in a narrow range, its  
downside limited amid wariness following the Bank of Japan's 
greenback-buying Monday, traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, financial markets in New York were closed Monday for a  
national holiday, leaving a dearth of news to affect trading. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was quoted at 124.81 yen, down  
from 125.57 yen late Monday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, prices dropped slightly on profit-taking,  
especially in blue-chip issues. The Nikkei average had gained 3.5 
percent in the three sessions prior to Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``As the recent pace of gains was fast, a brief pause was  
natural,'' said Kunihiro Hatae, general manager at Tokyo Securities 
Co. 
</P>
<P>
	But traders predicted the fall in stock prices would be limited.  
``Many investors want to buy actively if the Nikkei index nears the 
18,000 mark,'' Hatae said. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, the average surged after the Bank of Japan's  
quarterly ``tankan'' survey showed that business sentiment had 
improved in the past three months. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was down 0.78 points, or 0.05 percent, to 1,485.80. 
The TOPIX closed up 26.42 points, or 1.81 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose to 1.6300  
percent from Monday's finish of 1.6100 percent, driving its price 
down to 101.48 yen from 101.66 yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
