<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-05 05:50:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Centrica To Buy Brit Auto Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Centrica PLC, owner of British Gas, plans to buy  
Britain's Automobile Association for 1.1 billion pounds ($1.76 
billion), creating a business that offers a full range of services 
for home and car owners. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal announced Monday must be approved by AA members but is  
expected to be completed by the end of 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	The AA is the country's leading motoring organization and  
provides breakdown services for 9.5 million drivers. It earned a 
pretax profit in 1998 of 19.7 million pounds ($31.5 million) on 
sales of 627 million pounds ($1 billion). 
</P>
<P>
	Centrica sells gas and electricity to homes and businesses. It  
posted an operating profit last year of 208 million pounds ($333 
million) on sales of 7.48 billion pounds ($11.97 billion). 
</P>
<P>
	The two companies said they have similar operations in terms of  
marketing, phone call-in centers and management structure. 
</P>
<P>
	``We believe the acquisition offers clear benefits to both  
organizations,'' Centrica chief executive Roy Gardner said in a 
statement. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990705.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-05 20:10:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tomjanovich To Miss Oly. Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) -- Rudy Tomjanovich of the Houston  
Rockets is recovering from ``extreme physical exhaustion'' and 
won't coach the United States during an Olympic qualifying 
tournament this month. 
</P>
<P>
	Tomjanovich spent Friday and Saturday in the hospital, and  
Rockets team doctor Jim Muntz suggested that he take about a month 
off from work, according to team spokesman Tim Frank. 
</P>
<P>
	Philadelphia 76ers coach Larry Brown will replace Tomjanovich  
for the tournament in Puerto Rico on July 14-25, according to USA 
Basketball. But Tomjanovich apparently will still coach the U.S. 
team at the 2000 Olympics in Sydney, Australia. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've been given no indication by USA Basketball that this  
will affect Rudy's status for 2000,'' Frank said. 
</P>
<P>
	At a news conference Monday night at the Rockets' training  
center in Houston, Tomjanovich looked healthy but was low-key. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm disappointed and I'm going to do my best to recharge  
myself and get ready for the coming season,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The USA team, which begins training Tuesday, includes San  
Antonio's Tim Duncan and New York's Allan Houston. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States, which has won gold medals at the last two  
Olympics, must finish among the top two teams in the 10-team 
tournament to earn a berth in the 2000 Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
	Tomjanovich led a team of CBA and college players to a bronze  
medal at last summer's world championships in Greece. That team 
didn't have NBA players because of the lockout and wasn't expected 
to do that well. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown, who along with Purdue's Gene Keady and Kentucky's Tubby  
Smith were named as assistants, has served on three USA Basketball 
coaching staffs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
