<HEADLINE> Phillips Gets Career Hit No. 2,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Oakland second baseman Tony Phillips  
singled off the glove of Texas first baseman Lee Stevens to lead 
off the fourth inning Monday for his 2,000th career hit. 
</P>
<P>
	Phillips, a 16-year veteran, is currently hitting .244 on the  
season in his second tour of duty with the Athletics. 
</P>
